        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 27 at 6:07PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 607 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Kiowa, or 32 miles west of Limon, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Simla and Matheson.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
